<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-29T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-29T09:00:00-05:00" n="132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d132">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/125: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1" type="from">Grew</persName>) to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-29T23:00:00+09:00">June 29, 1932—11
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 29—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. Following telegram received from the Consul at Dairen: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“June 29, 4 p.m. Ex-commissioner <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_FJ1">Fukumoto</persName> relinquished
                                    custody of Dairen customhouse to British assistant. Former in
                                    new customhouse and depositing customs charges under his name
                                    Yokohama Specie Bank. Chinese that elected to work with new
                                    customhouse striking, disturbing traffic. In case goods pass
                                    through Dairen without duties payment at new customhouse, duties
                                    must be paid at Manchurian border or be detained.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GJC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>